.TH "ubifs_lpt_init" 9 "ubifs_lpt_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_lpt_init \- initialize the LPT.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubifs_lpt_init
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "int rd "  ","
.BI "int wr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "rd" 12
whether to initialize lpt for reading
.IP "wr" 12
whether to initialize lpt for writing
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For mounting 'rw', \fIrd\fP and \fIwr\fP are both true. For mounting 'ro', \fIrd\fP is true
and \fIwr\fP is false. For mounting from 'ro' to 'rw', \fIrd\fP is false and \fIwr\fP is
true.

This function returns 0 on success and a negative error code on failure.
